.SH PKG-CONFIG
.sp
If you’re not using CMake, use \fI\%pkg\-config\fP on the command line to set header and library paths:
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.nf
.ft C
gcc \-o hello_bson hello_bson.c $(pkg\-config \-\-libs \-\-cflags libbson\-1.0)

.ft P
.fi
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
